Of late I pass this place often. It's directly upstairs from the D line. Yesterday, we decided to partake in Comidas Criollas or creole food. The ladies at the counter were extremely welcoming. Everything displayed looked so tasty and inviting. We decided on roasted chicken with yautia also known as malanga which is a starchy root vegetable. We had that topped with pickled onions.We also had a salad and sweet plantains. For dessert we had flan. Each dish we selected was divine. Great experience and I'd definitely recommend.
